### Summary\n\nThe internal `copilot-utility-small` model family is resolved by `CopilotUtilitySmallChatEndpoint.resolve` (`copilotChatEndpoint.ts`), which hardcodes the CAPI family `gpt-4o-mini` **client-side** and calls `getChatModelFromCapiFamily('gpt-4o-mini')`. When a user's CAPI `/models` response contains no model in that family (plan/region/rollout differences, or a server-side rename or removal of the family), the lookup throws `Unable to resolve chat model with CAPI family selection: gpt-4o-mini` at `modelMetadataFetcher.ts:187`. Because this resolver — unlike its sibling `copilot-utility` family and unlike every override path in the same file — had **no fallback**, the exception propagates up through every background utility flow: commit-message generation (the dominant caller in the telemetry), branch-name generation, PR title/description, toolset grouping, rename suggestions, inline-chat progress messages, summarizer, title, and more.\n\nThe fix makes the small/fast resolver degrade to the API-marked base utility model (the same model that backs `copilot-utility`) when its preferred family is unavailable, instead of failing the whole flow.\n\nThis bucket is **pre-existing across all tracked extension versions** (0.49.0: 460 users, 0.50.1: 1049, 0.51.0: 1165, 0.52.0: 802). The apparent "0.52.0 spike" cited on the issue is a release-timing artifact: 0.51.2 was a short-lived two-day hotfix with low adoption, so any ratio measured against it is inflated. The underlying defect is long-standing, not a fresh 0.52.0 regression.\n\nFixes microsoft/vscode#321184\nRecommended reviewer: `@vritant24`\n\n### Culprit Commit\n\n`ef061ccb0fc47d4a94b2c0fa1f2ba80a3231979a` — *"Rename copilot-fast/copilot-base to copilot-utility-small/copilot-utility"* by **`@vritant24`** (2026-05-14).\n\nThis commit replaced the `ModelAliasRegistry` indirection with the dedicated `CopilotUtilitySmallChatEndpoint` / `CopilotUtilityChatEndpoint` resolver classes. Its own commit message states:\n\n> CopilotUtilitySmallChatEndpoint.resolve tries a small primary model and **falls back to a second small model if the primary is unavailable**.\n\n...but the shipped `resolve` contains **no such fallback** — the trailing "remove code smell" cleanups folded into the squash appear to have stripped it. The error bucket first appears in 0.49.0 (released 2026-05-20, immediately after this commit), consistent with this being the introducing change. The resolver class is present and unchanged in the shipped commit `6928394f91b684055b873eecb8bc281365131f1c`, so the culprit is an ancestor of the shipped build.\n\n### Code Flow\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A["_doGenerateCommitMessage (gitCommitMessageServiceImpl.ts:118)"] --> B["generateGitCommitMessage (gitCommitMessageGenerator.ts:36)"]\n    B --> C["endpointProvider.getChatEndpoint('copilot-utility-small')"]\n    C --> D["_resolveUtilityFamily (endpointProviderImpl.ts:163)"]\n    D --> E{"chat.utilitySmallModel override set?"}\n   
